subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis (modified from
Pleijel 1998
;
Parapar et al . 2004
): Ophiodrominae with uniform brown pigmentation occasionally with transversal whitish stripes; prostomium rounded to rectangular with facial tubercle, a pair of biarticulate palpi, and bearing three antennae, with the median antenna frontally inserted; six pairs of enlarged tentacular cirri; pharynx without papillae or jaws; prolonged neuropodial lobes; notopodia and notochaetae absent from segments 1 to 5 ; furcated and capillary simple notochaetae; composed neurochaetae.
